    "title" : "How to get SQLXML from OracleOpaque or alternatives?",
    "body" : "<p>I have a Java 21 Sping 3 project which uses ojdbc17 and Jakarta JMS libraries. It has a class which implements the org.springframework.jms.support.MessageConverter interface and its\n<code>Object fromMessage(Message msg)</code>\nmethod which contains following code snippet:</p>\n<pre><code>ORAData data = (ORAData) (AQjmsAdtMessage) msg).getAdtPayload();\nStruct struct = (Struct) data.toDatum(null);\nObject[] attributes = struct.getAttributes();\n[...]\nXMLType xml = XMLType.createXML((OPAQUE) attributes[4]);\nString payload = xml.getStringVal();\n</code></pre>\n<p>Both oracle.xdb.XMLType and oracle.sql.OPAQUE have become deprecated.</p>\n<p>I have searched the net for a new way to get the result of the last two code lines. From what I understood you now should use SQLXML and OracleOpaque instead but they're just interfaces, is there an example implementation which creates SQLXML from an OracleOpaque anywhere? Or is there a different way to do this?</p>\n",
